snippet.textDisplay:
2:18 A million versus a Billion.. Want to wrap your head around the differences in those numbers?  Okay lets do a little math using time, and you can follow along.

Lets convert how long 1 million seconds is.
1million ÷ 60 (seconds) ÷ 60 (minutes) ÷ 24 (hours) = 11.740 days, or 1 week, 4 days, and a little over 12 hours.

Now lets convert how long 1 billion seconds is.
1billion  ÷ 60 (seconds) ÷ 60 (minutes) ÷ 24 hours  ÷ 365.25 (year including leap year) is 31 years, plus another 7+ months

So if you're over 63 years old, you're 2billion seconds old.
